text:
It does not answer on its website I think so it doesn't answer.
I wanted to see if they had rangoli but the answer was off topic.
All around good.
Any India stuffs you get its a huge underground store. You need not go Tekah. Only thing is the stairs gg down as its a bomb shelter
Its fine, more Indian go-to groceries supplies. Not much of other options/varities.

I have been a regular customer of the store however past two times had really bad experience.
-billed for incorrect weight of items (I had to physically measure the items and prove to the store), later I got refund
-Provided expired Wheat flour pack and store has still not refunded the amount despite repeated follow-ups

Update as on 21st Feb:
-store has refunded the amount after this review
-I hope that store improves on their inventory management and customer care
